<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>Describes a mapping from a traditional combined image sampler uniform to binding points for a separate texture and sampler.</db:para>
<db:para>For example, if <db:code>combinedImageSampler</db:code> is <db:code>&quot;_54&quot;</db:code>, <db:code>textureBinding</db:code> is <db:code>1</db:code>, and <db:code>samplerBinding</db:code> is <db:code>2</db:code>, this means that the GLSL shader code contains a <db:code>sampler2D</db:code> (or sampler3D, etc.) uniform with the name of <db:code>_54</db:code> which corresponds to two separate resource bindings (<db:code>1</db:code> and <db:code>2</db:code>) in the original shader.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>This is a RHI API with limited compatibility guarantees, see <db:link xlink:href="qshader.xml">QShader</db:link> for details.</db:para>
</db:note>
</db:section>
